The scripts in this directory call a Maestro API which generates files in *.Properties format for the list of components provided.
This is a very heavy operation for the Maestro servers to process, so its important that this is not called in any automated sense.

The script generally takes around 45 minutes to run.
Please only run this script manually and as rarely as possible because it is one of the performance-impacting operations that Maestro does.


One other thing to be aware of - The scripts use component_name values to query the backend for each component. A problem may happen in that Component Names are not unique across the application.
This could result in the wrong Component and subsequently the wrong *.properties files being returned.
We could migrate the API to use component_id's instead (which are unique) but this would be some effort and its not deemed neccessary at this point.


Maestro Repo Link
https://github.azc.ext.hp.com/SWApps/maestro

Link to API call in Controller - the API is called "ComponentAsProperties"
https://github.azc.ext.hp.com/SWApps/maestro/blob/bab4b9192b341968a2221de4f6cdbf88130788fd/app/controllers/api/v1/export_controller.rb#L6
